docker build -t vue-pos .
Run your vue app container. => docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name vue-app vue-pos

-d means the container will run in the background
-p means port outsideport:insideport(nginx-80) 
--name means the container name
Finally write the image name

docker run -d --name my-postgres -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=mysecretpassword -p 5432:5432  postgres
<!-- docker run -d --name my-postgres -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=mysecretpassword -p 5432:5432 postgres -->
docker network create my_net
docker run --name my-postgres --network  my_net -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=mysecretpassword -p 5432:5432  postgres

docker run -d --network my_net -p 8080:80 --name frontend vue-app(finally run)

Check if it's running => docker ps
View container logs => docker logs vue-app
Stop the container => docker stop vue-app
Start it again => docker start vue-app
Remove the container (after stopping it) => docker rm vue-app
Build again with a different name => docker build -t vue-pos-v2 .
Run with different port (e.g., port 3000) => docker run -d -p 3000:80 --name vue-app-2 vue-pos

        Push to Docker Hub
Tag your image => docker tag vue-pos yourusername/vue-pos:latest   
Login to Docker Hub => docker login     
Push to Docker Hub => docker push yourusername/vue-pos:latest

